<a name="wp1162111"> </a><h3 class="pHeading2">
Tuning Actions
</h3>
<hr />
<a name="wp1162113"> </a><p class="pBody">
Tuning a PID (proportional-integral-derivative) controller usually involves disturbing the process and observing the response of the control system to the process. This is undesirable with many processes, especially turbines. For tuning to be effective, it must be performed under normal process conditions, with normal flows through valves, and driving a normal load.
</p>
